16
00:00:12,347 --> 00:00:12,463
http://hiqve.com

17
00:00:12,464 --> 00:00:12,581
http://hiqve.com/

18
00:00:12,582 --> 00:00:15,582
http://hiqve.com/

19
00:00:18,606 --> 00:00:19,982
<i>Secret weapons!</i>

20
00:00:20,691 --> 00:00:22,777
<i>The Jedi Council deploys a squad of droids</i>

21
00:00:22,818 --> 00:00:25,613
<i>on a desperate mission
aboard a Separatist cruiser.</i>

22
00:00:26,030 --> 00:00:28,491
<i>Under the guidance
of Colonel Meebur Gascon,</i>

23
00:00:28,616 --> 00:00:32,036
<i>the droids succeed in stealing
a crucial encryption module.</i>

24
00:00:32,537 --> 00:00:37,291
<i>Now the Colonel and his droid squad
must return the module to the Jedi Temple</i>

25
00:00:37,333 --> 00:00:42,296
<i>to crack a Separatist code detailing an
impending terror plot against the Republic.</i>

26
00:00:45,800 --> 00:00:49,136
How long until my command center
is operational again?

27
00:00:51,806 --> 00:00:52,932
Okay, fine.

28
00:00:54,308 --> 00:00:58,854
I meant, how long
until Beezee is operational again?

29
00:01:00,606 --> 00:01:01,857
Well, make it fast!

30
00:01:02,275 --> 00:01:06,362
We must get this encryption module
back to the Republic as soon as possible.

31
00:01:18,499 --> 00:01:19,709
Uh-oh!

32
00:01:29,343 --> 00:01:31,846
Oh, Beezee! You are all better!

33
00:01:32,054 --> 00:01:37,018
WAC, what are you doing back here?
Who is flying this shuttle?

34
00:01:37,685 --> 00:01:39,770
I have good news and bad news, Colonel.

35
00:01:39,854 --> 00:01:43,024
The bad news is,
scans are picking up giant ice formations

36
00:01:43,149 --> 00:01:44,442
commonly called comets

37
00:01:44,525 --> 00:01:46,611
-heading straight for us.
-What?

38
00:01:48,029 --> 00:01:50,031
What in the world is the good news?

39
00:01:50,531 --> 00:01:53,701
At least you have a good excuse
if your mission is a failure?

40
00:01:54,035 --> 00:01:56,329
Get out of my way.

41
00:02:08,382 --> 00:02:10,343
Quick! Drop us out of hyperspace!

42
00:02:17,683 --> 00:02:18,726
Whoa!

43
00:02:23,230 --> 00:02:24,231
Look out!

44
00:02:37,119 --> 00:02:38,454
The shuttle's power system

45
00:02:38,537 --> 00:02:39,580
has been knocked out.

46
00:02:39,747 --> 00:02:41,290
I can see that!

47
00:02:45,169 --> 00:02:46,504
He says he can fix it.

48
00:03:07,692 --> 00:03:09,318
And swinging right...

49
00:03:22,665 --> 00:03:24,667
Auxiliary power has been restored,

50
00:03:24,750 --> 00:03:26,502
but it is not enough to get us moving!

51
00:03:26,585 --> 00:03:29,296
We need the primary motivators
re-established now!

52
00:03:29,588 --> 00:03:31,757
Forget that!
We need the engines to come on!

53
00:03:32,049 --> 00:03:33,759
That's what I'm saying!

54
00:03:44,812 --> 00:03:46,814
Uh-oh. They just got bigger!

55
00:03:48,524 --> 00:03:50,443
Come on, you lousy mechs!

56
00:03:55,865 --> 00:03:57,992
Colonel, we are headed for that comet!

57
00:03:58,576 --> 00:03:59,660
Brace yourself!

58
00:04:04,540 --> 00:04:06,000
The engines are back online!

59
00:04:39,241 --> 00:04:40,284
Whoa! Whoa!

60
00:05:09,563 --> 00:05:12,608
We have lost the stabilizers
and primary control of the engines.

61
00:05:14,735 --> 00:05:16,570
We are going to have to put her down
on that planet.

62
00:05:19,990 --> 00:05:22,451
What planet is it?
Is it Separatist-controlled?

63
00:05:22,576 --> 00:05:24,578
-Who cares?
-I care!

64
00:05:24,662 --> 00:05:28,916
-We can't jeopardize the mission !
-I think we are past that point, sir.

65
00:05:53,315 --> 00:05:55,442
We're going down!

66
00:06:13,335 --> 00:06:15,546
I think I ruptured my gizzard.

67
00:06:44,241 --> 00:06:47,828
Well, this is a fine mess
you mechs got us into.

68
00:06:50,831 --> 00:06:57,588
Look at this! All the database says is
"Abafar: Information on planet void."

69
00:07:00,007 --> 00:07:05,179
Don't be absurd ! We can't just
go rushing off like fools into this void!

70
00:07:05,346 --> 00:07:08,766
We need to stay put, consider all the facts,
and then I'll...

71
00:07:09,016 --> 00:07:11,393
I'll draw up a reconnaissance plan
and we can...

72
00:07:11,518 --> 00:07:14,521
Hey! Hey! Where are you going, soldier?

73
00:07:16,398 --> 00:07:18,567
He says we have to finish our mission.

74
00:07:23,030 --> 00:07:27,368
Hey! Where did you get that?
That is classified material!

75
00:07:30,079 --> 00:07:33,082
I will not stand for insubordination!

76
00:07:33,415 --> 00:07:34,583
Do not worry, Colonel,

77
00:07:34,708 --> 00:07:37,795
I can lead the mission from here
and return the module.

78
00:07:38,128 --> 00:07:40,756
Maybe they'll give me a promotion!

79
00:07:41,382 --> 00:07:43,634
Over my dead body!

80
00:07:43,884 --> 00:07:45,469
Beezee! Pop your top!

81
00:07:45,970 --> 00:07:50,057
I will not let you droids
commandeer my mission!

82
00:08:18,669 --> 00:08:20,796
Oh, so hot.

83
00:08:24,967 --> 00:08:29,805
I can't believe I came this close
to completing my first mission,

84
00:08:29,930 --> 00:08:33,350
only to get lost in this detestable desert.

85
00:08:33,851 --> 00:08:35,352
Look on the bright side, Colonel.

86
00:08:35,436 --> 00:08:37,479
At least it is a sunny day.

87
00:08:37,938 --> 00:08:40,441
What sun? I don't see any sun.

88
00:08:40,983 --> 00:08:43,318
It's just hot and oppressive.

89
00:08:44,361 --> 00:08:45,654
Wait a minute.

90
00:08:46,363 --> 00:08:47,656
There's no sun.

91
00:08:47,948 --> 00:08:50,200
How do we know
which direction we're going?

92
00:08:51,994 --> 00:08:55,372
You set your directional guidance
to "straight"?

93
00:08:55,789 --> 00:09:00,127
That's all we're going on,
some rudimentary programming directive

94
00:09:00,169 --> 00:09:02,337
in a lousy astromech?

95
00:09:06,759 --> 00:09:09,762
Yes! I know you're designed for navigation.

96
00:09:09,803 --> 00:09:13,474
But that requires map coordinates
and environmental input,

97
00:09:13,599 --> 00:09:16,268
something we are sorely lacking here.

98
00:09:16,810 --> 00:09:19,438
All right, we can't rely on technology.

99
00:09:20,022 --> 00:09:21,899
We have to rely on my training,

100
00:09:22,316 --> 00:09:24,526
something you droids don't have.

101
00:09:25,569 --> 00:09:27,029
How do you know, Colonel?

102
00:09:28,655 --> 00:09:30,908
Because droids don't get training!

103
00:09:31,075 --> 00:09:32,659
You get programmed.

104
00:09:34,161 --> 00:09:35,662
That's your weakness!

105
00:09:36,205 --> 00:09:40,084
So how is your training
going to lead us out of this void?

106
00:09:41,085 --> 00:09:45,172
Well,
my training as an officer tells me

107
00:09:45,255 --> 00:09:51,345
to use all available resources
to stay alive until help comes.

108
00:09:51,428 --> 00:09:55,015
So, your officer training,
how exactly did you learn that?

109
00:09:55,349 --> 00:09:57,768
It was drilled into me by my superior.

110
00:09:58,769 --> 00:10:01,438
Then you were programmed, just like us.

111
00:10:01,688 --> 00:10:05,526
What? No!
I am not like you droids in any way.

112
00:10:06,026 --> 00:10:08,612
I can think outside my program,

113
00:10:08,695 --> 00:10:10,364
I mean, my training,

114
00:10:10,447 --> 00:10:14,868
and I can make decisions
based on a complex analysis of a situation.

115
00:10:15,077 --> 00:10:18,622
Which is why I insist we return to the ship.

116
00:10:19,039 --> 00:10:21,875
Wait a minute. Why can't I find our tracks?

117
00:10:22,417 --> 00:10:24,461
-There are not any.
-What?

118
00:10:25,087 --> 00:10:28,298
I noticed it earlier.
This surface leaves no trace of us.

119
00:10:29,049 --> 00:10:30,759
You noticed it earlier?

120
00:10:30,884 --> 00:10:33,971
Why in the world didn't you say anything?

121
00:10:34,471 --> 00:10:36,557
I did not think we would want
to go backwards

122
00:10:36,598 --> 00:10:39,643
when forward seems to be the only way
out of this void.

123
00:10:41,145 --> 00:10:46,400
Why are you thinking? I don't want you
to think. Thinking is my job.

124
00:10:46,483 --> 00:10:48,569
I am the commanding officer.

125
00:10:48,610 --> 00:10:50,571
You are just a pilot!

126
00:10:50,988 --> 00:10:52,990
Oh. That hurt.

127
00:10:55,826 --> 00:11:00,122
- I have been thinking, Colonel.
- I told you not to do that.

128
00:11:01,123 --> 00:11:03,917
My programming keeps me focused
on the task at hand,

129
00:11:03,959 --> 00:11:06,378
which means I do not have to worry
about my health,

130
00:11:06,420 --> 00:11:08,297
I just have to worry about the mission.

131
00:11:08,422 --> 00:11:10,090
Don't even go there.

132
00:11:10,549 --> 00:11:13,135
-So I think...
-Don't do that!

133
00:11:13,594 --> 00:11:16,054
...when you die, I should lead D Squad.

134
00:11:16,972 --> 00:11:18,765
Stop!

135
00:11:21,727 --> 00:11:23,270
You are what's killing me!

136
00:11:23,395 --> 00:11:26,773
I can't believe I am forced
to justify my existence

137
00:11:26,940 --> 00:11:28,442
with a droid!

138
00:11:28,567 --> 00:11:31,778
I'm at the end ! I can feel it!

139
00:11:31,820 --> 00:11:36,283
All I ask is that you just let me die
with dignity!

140
00:11:36,825 --> 00:11:38,118
Is that possible?

141
00:11:42,247 --> 00:11:44,249
What? Our ship?

142
00:11:50,130 --> 00:11:52,424
You stupid, lucky droids!

143
00:11:52,466 --> 00:11:56,011
You have just taken us in a circle!

144
00:12:06,480 --> 00:12:09,149
Wait a minute. Is this really our ship?

145
00:12:10,943 --> 00:12:12,611
How long have we been gone?

146
00:12:19,785 --> 00:12:20,827
Ugh!

147
00:12:23,163 --> 00:12:24,831
No, it is not our ship.

148
00:12:24,873 --> 00:12:27,000
No. No, no!

149
00:12:27,042 --> 00:12:29,169
No, no, no!

150
00:12:35,175 --> 00:12:38,470
Artoo is right. This is what happens
when you stay at the ship.

151
00:12:40,138 --> 00:12:43,934
Why is this happening to me?

152
00:13:15,882 --> 00:13:18,802
Maybe he is going to jump
and put himself out of his misery.

153
00:13:21,013 --> 00:13:24,224
Well, I vote for myself
as the new leader of this mission.

154
00:13:28,353 --> 00:13:33,233
You cannot vote for Artoo. He is just
a mech. He cannot lead a squadron.

155
00:13:35,569 --> 00:13:36,862
Help!

156
00:13:38,864 --> 00:13:42,576
There has to be something out there!

157
00:13:43,160 --> 00:13:45,037
Show me a sign,

158
00:13:46,038 --> 00:13:47,581
a glimmer of hope!

159
00:13:54,713 --> 00:13:56,923
I do not know who he is talking to.

160
00:13:57,257 --> 00:13:58,884
Maybe whoever programmed him.

161
00:14:11,021 --> 00:14:14,941
There! I see something !
Oh, a village!

162
00:14:24,117 --> 00:14:27,746
What are you waiting for?
We're saved !

163
00:14:46,264 --> 00:14:48,141
What exactly do you see, Colonel?

164
00:14:48,975 --> 00:14:51,144
I don't know. Hard to say.

165
00:14:51,728 --> 00:14:54,606
An outpost. Maybe a cant in a.

166
00:14:55,524 --> 00:14:57,442
Whatever it is, they can help us.

167
00:15:03,698 --> 00:15:06,076
I do not see anything either, Artoo.

168
00:15:06,493 --> 00:15:07,869
He should've jumped.

169
00:15:36,440 --> 00:15:37,524
No.

170
00:15:37,941 --> 00:15:40,819
We're going in circles again!

171
00:15:57,210 --> 00:16:00,672
I agree.
We cannot trust his training anymore.

172
00:16:01,173 --> 00:16:03,383
But I cannot trust
your programming, either,

173
00:16:03,967 --> 00:16:07,095
especially if you will not vote for me
to be the new leader.

174
00:16:08,847 --> 00:16:10,265
Where are you going now?

175
00:16:13,685 --> 00:16:15,353
Hey! That is not true!

176
00:16:15,687 --> 00:16:17,939
I am more than just a pilot!

177
00:16:23,445 --> 00:16:25,238
We need a new plan, Colonel.

178
00:16:25,655 --> 00:16:28,700
I just realized. What if I'm dead?

179
00:16:29,868 --> 00:16:35,624
What if I died in that shuttle crash
and now I'm stuck here in limbo?

180
00:16:36,124 --> 00:16:37,250
Yes.

181
00:16:37,667 --> 00:16:39,336
I should have gone with the mechs.

182
00:16:41,046 --> 00:16:43,131
Think about it. Life.

183
00:16:43,381 --> 00:16:45,008
Life is a void.

184
00:16:45,258 --> 00:16:48,887
We search and search for answers,
but there are none.

185
00:16:49,054 --> 00:16:51,389
Hope is just an illusion, WAC.

186
00:16:51,640 --> 00:16:54,518
Death is the only certainty!

187
00:16:56,019 --> 00:16:58,188
Giving up is not in my programming.

188
00:16:59,147 --> 00:17:01,441
I am surprised that it is in yours, Colonel.

189
00:17:10,242 --> 00:17:11,701
Maybe...

190
00:17:12,410 --> 00:17:13,620
Maybe you're right.

191
00:17:13,703 --> 00:17:17,916
I was taught to find a rational solution
to every problem.

192
00:17:18,542 --> 00:17:19,918
But this void,

193
00:17:20,293 --> 00:17:23,213
this proves that that's not always possible.

194
00:17:24,422 --> 00:17:26,883
Maybe I need to change how I see things,

195
00:17:27,133 --> 00:17:30,387
and that will change my programming,
my training.

196
00:17:31,972 --> 00:17:33,014
You know what?

197
00:17:33,348 --> 00:17:35,850
You are more than just a pilot, WAC.

198
00:17:36,268 --> 00:17:38,937
I knew it! I knew it!

199
00:17:40,814 --> 00:17:43,775
All right, all righty, calm down, soldier.

200
00:18:05,046 --> 00:18:06,464
Whoa! Whoa!

201
00:18:12,637 --> 00:18:14,472
This is our way out of the void!

202
00:18:14,848 --> 00:18:16,683
You have lost your mind, Colonel!

203
00:18:17,309 --> 00:18:20,186
No! This is our only hope!

204
00:18:20,312 --> 00:18:24,482
We've got to stop following my training
or your programming

205
00:18:24,566 --> 00:18:27,110
and follow the birds' instincts!

206
00:18:27,485 --> 00:18:28,737
Grab hold!

207
00:18:30,071 --> 00:18:31,698
Like this? Whoa!

208
00:18:58,391 --> 00:18:59,643
Look!

209
00:19:00,977 --> 00:19:02,604
I can see a town from here!

210
00:19:07,317 --> 00:19:08,985
You can see that, right?

211
00:19:12,113 --> 00:19:13,198
I sure can!

212
00:19:13,573 --> 00:19:17,035
How did you know, Colonel, that these
creatures would get us out of the void?

213
00:19:17,118 --> 00:19:21,539
You've got your
programming, I've got my training.

214
00:19:21,748 --> 00:19:24,793
But these creatures,
they have their instincts!

215
00:19:25,043 --> 00:19:27,253
They know how to survive out here!

216
00:19:27,712 --> 00:19:28,880
If you say so.

217
00:20:10,588 --> 00:20:14,300
I don't believe it.
Those mechs beat us here!

218
00:20:15,343 --> 00:20:17,554
Stupid, lucky droids.

219
00:20:18,096 --> 00:20:19,639
Just like you said, Colonel.

220
00:20:20,557 --> 00:20:21,599
Tell you what, WAC.

221
00:20:22,308 --> 00:20:24,602
Why don't you get the squad ready to roll?

222
00:20:25,437 --> 00:20:28,022
I've got a second chance
to complete this mission

223
00:20:28,106 --> 00:20:30,358
and I intend to take advantage of it,

224
00:20:30,942 --> 00:20:33,611
after I rehydrate myself.

225
00:20:34,571 --> 00:20:35,613
That'll be all,

226
00:20:35,697 --> 00:20:36,740
Corporal.

227
00:20:39,409 --> 00:20:40,535
Corporal?

228
00:20:40,869 --> 00:20:44,122
Yes, sir! The squad will be ready to roll.

229
00:20:45,999 --> 00:20:47,959
Attention!

230
00:20:48,251 --> 00:20:50,670
Front and center, soldiers!

231
00:20:50,754 --> 00:20:54,424
I want us ready to roll ! Pronto! Pronto!

232
00:20:57,761 --> 00:21:00,805
That is "Corporal WAC" to you, soldier!

233
00:21:01,055 --> 00:21:04,642
And I will not tolerate insubordination!

234
00:21:06,293 --> 00:21:11,293
http://hiqve.com/

